27/03/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Anti-corruption prosecutors announced on Thursday (March 26th) they have launched a corruption investigation of interior ministry intelligence chief Cornel Serban and businessman Gabriel Popoviciu over their involvement in shadowy real estate deals. Officials say Serban and another official at the interior ministry's anti-corruption department, Petru Pitcovici, tried to block an investigation of a real estate deal involving Popoviciu and the former rector of Bucharest's Agronomy University, Ioan Alecu. The deal involved a 220ha land plot in Baneasa, a wealthy suburb of Bucharest, for which buyers greatly underpaid. (Cotidianul - 27/03/09; AP, News In - 26/03/09)
